        "p": "When discussing wall clock placement in the bedroom as per Vastu, numerous questions arise from individuals eager to perfect their home's energetic blueprint. Here are some of the most frequently asked questions and their detailed answers to help clarify this nuanced subject.\n\nQuestion 1: Can I place a wall clock above the bedroom door?\nAnswer: According to Vastu Shastra, placing a wall clock directly above any doorway, particularly the bedroom door, is strictly discouraged. Doorways are active portals where energy enters and exits a room. Hanging a clock above this transitional space disrupts the flow of incoming positive energy, essentially \"cutting\" the aura of anyone walking underneath it. This can lead to a pervasive sense of anxiety, constant rushing, and unexpected delays in personal and professional endeavors. Always choose a solid, unobstructed wall, preferably in the North or East, for your timepiece.\n\nQuestion 2: Does the material of the clock affect the Vastu of the bedroom?\nAnswer: Yes, the material of the clock significantly influences the elemental balance of the room. Metallic clocks, particularly those made of brass, copper, or steel, are excellent for the Northern wall as they resonate with the Water and Space elements, promoting clarity and financial flow. Wooden clocks are highly recommended for the Eastern wall, as wood represents the Air and Earth elements, fostering growth, health, and family harmony. Avoid clocks made of cheap, degraded plastics or those with overly dark, heavy metallic finishes, as they can emanate dense, stagnant energy.\n\nQuestion 3: What should I do if my bedroom clock stops working?\nAnswer: A stopped clock is considered a major Vastu defect, often referred to as \"dead energy.\" A clock that fails to keep time symbolizes stalled progress, blocked opportunities, and stagnant life force. If a clock stops working, you must either replace the batteries and repair it immediately or remove it from the bedroom altogether. Keeping broken timepieces, or clocks with cracked glass, attracts negative vibrations and can directly impact your health and prosperity.\n\nQuestion 4: Are digital clocks better than analog clocks for bedroom Vastu?\nAnswer: Analog clocks with a continuous sweep motion (non-ticking) are generally preferred in Vastu because the circular movement of the hands symbolizes the natural, continuous cycle of time and the universe. Digital clocks, while functional, lack this circular, flowing energy. However, if you choose a digital clock, ensure the display is not overly bright or emitting harsh red light, which can disrupt sleep patterns and introduce fiery, aggressive energy into a restful space."
